[Mayor's Mansion]

110
00:08:02,350 --> 00:08:03,000
What?

111
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:04,560
Weren't you pretty happy

112
00:08:04,560 --> 00:08:06,080
when we were on the branch just now?

113
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,960
Why are you throwing up after the ride instead?

114
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:14,810
It's all because your ride was so bumpy.

115
00:08:15,970 --> 00:08:18,360
You are the first one who

116
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:19,760
dares to talk to me like this.

117
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,560
No wonder you dared to assassinate me.

118
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:23,880
That is a...

119
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:33,600
I didn't.

120
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:34,640
That's a misunderstanding.

121
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,280
It's up to me to decide whether it's a misunderstanding or not.

122
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:40,240
According to the laws of Dongsheng,

123
00:08:40,640 --> 00:08:44,160
those who try to assassinate me will have their hearts and eyes gouged out,

124
00:08:44,250 --> 00:08:45,830
their entire family punished,

125
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,760
and be executed via prolonged torture.

126
00:08:56,090 --> 00:08:57,450
What did you say?

127
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,840
The trap is just a misunderstanding.

128
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,120
How could that turn into an execution?

129
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:02,660
It's all because the guard next to you

130
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:03,730
threatened me with a knife.

131
00:09:04,850 --> 00:09:05,650
Oh, right.

132
00:09:05,690 --> 00:09:07,230
If he hadn't scared me in the first place,

133
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,640
I wouldn't have stepped on that trap.

134
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:10,720
Kill him if you want.

135
00:09:10,740 --> 00:09:11,990
Kill him ruthlessly.

136
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,280
I can consider not killing you,

137
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:17,370
and let bygones be bygones.

138
00:09:17,530 --> 00:09:20,520
But you have to promise me one thing.

139
00:09:20,830 --> 00:09:22,560
Be my private entertainer.

140
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:24,630
Private entertainer?

141
00:09:27,440 --> 00:09:28,400
For how long?

142
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,870
For as long as I tell you to.

143
00:09:31,580 --> 00:09:33,790
So, isn't that akin to selling myself to you?

144
00:09:34,570 --> 00:09:35,620
Absolutely not.

145
00:09:36,300 --> 00:09:37,740
If you disagree,

146
00:09:38,380 --> 00:09:42,130
I'll convict you for trying to assassinate me.

147
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:44,000
Go ahead then.

148
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:47,290
A soldier can be killed but not humiliated.

149
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,200
Fine.

150
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:49,840
Xiaoqi.

151
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:54,120
She will be executed at noon tomorrow.

152
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,740
Are you really going to execute me?

153
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:56,950
Of course.

154
00:09:56,950 --> 00:09:57,560
Come in!

155
00:09:59,150 --> 00:09:59,950
Wait.

156
00:09:59,970 --> 00:10:00,770
W-wait!

157
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:01,760
Wait, wait!

158
00:10:02,250 --> 00:10:03,050
Wait a minute!

159
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:09,540
Let's talk this over.

160
00:10:09,680 --> 00:10:12,120
Regarding the duration...

161
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:15,420
One year?

162
00:10:18,210 --> 00:10:19,430
Two years?

163
00:10:23,610 --> 00:10:24,450
Four years?

164
00:10:28,950 --> 00:10:29,670
Five years?

165
00:10:30,020 --> 00:10:31,190
Five years, okay?

166
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:38,800
Who was the one who just said,

167
00:10:38,820 --> 00:10:40,260
"A soldier can be killed

168
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:41,760
but not humiliated?"

169
00:10:43,730 --> 00:10:44,890
Take her away.

170
00:10:45,170 --> 00:10:45,930
Help!

171
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:46,840
I'm innocent!

172
00:10:46,890 --> 00:10:48,050
Help!

173
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,140
Young Lord, you're disregarding human lives!

174
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,350
Mu!

175
00:11:09,730 --> 00:11:10,450
Mu!

176
00:11:23,210 --> 00:11:23,980
Mu!

177
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:28,100
Listen up.

178
00:11:28,350 --> 00:11:29,560
If anything happens to Mu,

179
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:30,510
I won't forgive you!

180
00:11:30,830 --> 00:11:31,530
Yes.

181
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,210
Mu!

182
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:37,110
Mu!

183
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:39,880
Mu!

184
00:11:43,510 --> 00:11:44,110
Mu!

185
00:11:44,140 --> 00:11:45,210
Are you okay, Mu?

186
00:11:46,860 --> 00:11:48,120
Are you hurt anywhere?

187
